<BODY>
<H1><A HREF="http://www.w3.org/"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://www.w3.org/Icons/WWW/w3c_home" ALT="W3C" WIDTH="72" HEIGHT="48" align="middle"></A> CSS1 Test Suite</H1>

<P>
The CSS1 Test Suite is provided as a way for vendors and page authors to test their browser's conformance to the CSS1 specification.  This test suite is organized around individual properties of Cascading Style Sheets, Level 1 (CSS1).  In order to use it most effectively, you will <STRONG>NEED</STRONG> to make sure that you have completely read and understood the contents of <A HREF="sec00.htm">Prologue</A> before you start testing any user agent.
</P>
<P>
For each property, there is at least one page which tests the property's values in various combinations, using HTML 4.0 markup.  The test pages are broken out into a number of sections which reflect the structure of the CSS1 specification itself, in addition to a Prologue and a few appendicies.
</P>

